kodkod.engine.fol2sat

Class TranslationRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • kodkod.engine.fol2sat.TranslationRecord

  • public abstract class TranslationRecord
extends Object
    Record of a translation event. Each translation event is described by four pieces of information:
    1. the formula that was translated;
    2. the node from which the translated formula was derived by skolemization or through some other optimization;
    3. the environment in which the given formula is translated, given as a binding of free variables to scalars (singleton, unary tuplesets);
    4. the CNF literal, expressed as an integer, that represents the meaning of the given formula in the given environment.
    Author:
    Emina Torlak
    Specfields:
    node: Node // node that was transformed to this.translated
    translated: Formula // the translated formula obtain from this.node
    literal: int // cnf literal representing the meaning of this.node in this.env
    env: Variable ->one TupleSet // bindings for free, non-skolemized variables // for which this.node (or its desugared form) evaluates to this.literal
